When to Use DynamoDB:
Based on this exercise, when would you choose DynamoDB over PostgreSQL?
What are the key trade-offs?
Based on this exercise, I’d choose DynamoDB over PostgreSQL when I need:
high scalability,
very fast read/write performance,
and when my access patterns are clearly defined in advance.
If I need complex joins or ad-hoc analytics, PostgreSQL would still be better.
So the main trade-off is: DynamoDB gives speed and scalability, while PostgreSQL gives flexibility and complex querying power.


